cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CV 

The paper proposes specialized embeddings for bipartite graphs that are particularly useful in recommender systems, data visualization, and drug discovery. These applications are typically associated with machine learning and data mining, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed embeddings on link prediction and recommendation tasks, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI) research. The use of algebraic distance on graphs also suggests a potential connection to graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), while the application to data visualization may indicate a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
